\'d only need 1 generic hover script. Because I couldn\'t find a script, I decided to give it a try myself. My naming scheme:\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-414\" alt=\"ps layer button hover\" src=\"http://ptrck.nl/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ps-layer-button-hover-300x57.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"57\" />\r\n\r\nNormal layer name: ButtonA\r\nHover state Layer: ButtonA hover\r\n\r\nSo for hovers I duplicate a Layer Group, and add \' hover\' at the end of its name. A Framer script will automatically hide the hover layers and add the mouseover functionality.\r\n\r\nIt works! I\'m not a developer, so please don\'t mind the crappy scripting. For testing purposes it gets the job done. <a href=\"http://db.tt/K4pQ93kF\">Download my app.js hover script</a> and give it a try.\r\n\r\nStuff I\'d like to be added:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>cursor change on mouseover</li>\r\n	<li>active states on mousedown, similar to hover states on mouseover</li>\r\n	<li>proper retina viewport scale (workaround: zoom out 4x in Safari with cmd +)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWould love to hear about existing scripts, or ways to improve it.\r\n\r\nRead more about Framer on <a href=\"https://medium.com/look-what-i-made/95d2682d07\">Koen\'s announcement on Medium</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.framerjs.com/\">Download FramerJS </a>and check it out','Prototyping hover states in Photoshop with Framer JS','','inherit','open','open','','412-revision-v1','','','2013-09-11 12:39:22','2013-09-11 11:39:22','',412,'http://ptrck.nl/412-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(428,1,'2013-09-11 15:58:49','2013-09-11 14:58:49','Wow, just found out about <a href=\"http://www.framerjs.com/\">Framer.js</a>. An awesome prototype companion for Photoshop built by <a href=\"http://koenbok.com\">Koen Bok</a>. It allows you to create quality interactive mockups in your browser.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Framer - Prototyping Tool\" href=\"http://www.framerjs.com\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-418\" alt=\"framerlogo\" src=\"http://pt